100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 1, 1926, the British Empire faced mounting tensions as the Irish Free State continued to grapple with its independence, while in the United States, Prohibition remained a contentious issue, drawing ire from many citizens. In global affairs, the League of Nations struggled to assert its influence amid rising political unrest in Europe. Additionally, the world was abuzz with technological advancements, with radio broadcasts gaining popularity, heralding a new era in communication.
